GraphicalEditPart#getModelChildren()'s implementation [return new ArrayList(((View)model).getVisibleChildren())] will cause the removal of 'invisible' editparts.
If you have installed a ConnectionLabelsEditPolicy on a shapeeditpart, the show/hide connector labels [HideConnectionLabelsAction] will be permantly disabled once you hide the connector labels from that shape since the shape's label editpart will be been set invisible and the subsequent call to refreshChildren() will trigger the removal of the editpart.
This is not a problem with connectors since ConnectionEditPart#getModelChildren will return ((View) getModel()).getChildren();

