When using the internal builder it ignores most of the macros used when defining the commands for the build tools. For example this is the default g++ build command setting:
${COMMAND} ${FLAGS} ${OUTPUT_FLAG}${OUTPUT_PREFIX}${OUTPUT} ${INPUTS}

This works with the standard make builder
${COMMAND} ${FLAGS} ${OUTPUT_FLAG}${OUTPUT_PREFIX}${OUTPUT} ${InputFileRelPath}

With the internal builder the macro is not expanded. The command the internal builder tries to execute still contains "${InputFileRelPath}" as a string. Furthermore other useful macros like ${DirectoryDelimiter} do not work too. 

(My actual problem is that the internal builder uses backslashes. This doesn't work for me because my eclipse runs on win32 but the build command is executed via plink on a remote machine that expects slashes.)

